<TITLE> Police arrest 16 in overnight raid on CU halls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 16 (bdnews24.com) Police detained 16 students after raiding six dormitories and two cottages of Chittagong University early on Saturday. Hathazari police chief Md Ismail told bdnews24.com that the detainees would be shown arrested after scrutiny. During the raid from midnight on Friday to 3am on Saturday police also recovered scores of sticks, hockey sticks and rods used in the clash between the two student organisations that left at least 25 injured on Thursday. CU proctor Dr Mohammad Jashimuddin said the university administration assisted police in the raid. Vice-chancellor Dr Abu Yusuf said the raid was carried out at the directives of the higher authorities of the law enforcers to maintain academic atmosphere on the campus. Authorities earlier called off classes and examinations until May 21 on Friday. The university administration at an emergency meeting chaired by the VC also formed a three-strong committee headed by Dr Kamal Hossain to identify the perpetrators and take action. The other members were Chittagong University Teachers' Association general secretary Dr Quamrul Huda and provost of Khaleda Zia Hall Dr Mohiuddin. Another three-member committee was formed to encourage student organisations to co-exist peacefully in the halls. Pro-vice-chancellor Dr Mohammed Alauddin is the convener of the committee and Dr Md Nurul Anwar and professor Hasan Mahmud are the members. Of the injured, 17 were activists of pro-Awami League Bangladesh Chhatra League and six of Jama'at-e-Islami-backed Islami Chhatra Shibir, Ismail, the officer in charge of Hathazari Police Station, said. A personal assistant to the university vice-chancellor was also injured in the clash. The BCL activists injured in the clash are Jahid, Shanto, Sajib, Bacchu, Tareq, Maruf, Shihab, Babul, Abeer, Sujan, Pipu, Saiful, Sajib, Sazid, Dipan, Rakib and Imtiajur Rahman. The ICS workers who sustained injuries are Mansurul Alam Majumder, president of Suhrawardy Hall, Maruf Billah and Abdul Alim Nesar Ahmed Niazi, Mostofa Saker Ullah and Shahed. All of the injured BCL students were admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital, while half of the injured Shibir workers were admitted to the same hospital, he said. The condition of BCL's Jahid and Abdur Rab Hall president Maruf and Mansurul Alam Majumder of ICS were critical. The clash broke out at one stage of arguments at 10:30pm on Thursday at Shahid Abdur Rab Hall when BCL activists had gone to protest ICS provocation and organisational activities in mosque, the OC further said. The vice-chancellor told bdnews24.com that one of personal secretaries sustained a head injury. They unruly students vandalised his car and a motorcycle and the halls, he further said. The BCL activists beat up the university correspondent of Daily Amar Desh, Rashed Khan Menon on Friday evening. bdnews24.c
